    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1960-03-28T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-02-11T00:00:00-05:00"
                n="[Unnumbered document following Document 710 (#40)]" subtype="editorial-note"
                type="document" xml:id="d710a-40">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Editor’s Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>—No official record of this conversation has been found. The following subjects
                    were discussed: allocation of shipping for civilian and military
                        passengers;<note n="2" xml:id="d710a-40fn2">The discussion of this subject
                        presumably centered on the report of the Combined Transportation Committee
                        which was circulated on July 21 as <gloss target="#t_CCS1">C. C. S.</gloss>
                        897. See <ref target="#d1192">document No. 1192</ref>, <hi rend="italic"
                            >post</hi>.</note> extension of the time during which the United States
                    should have the use of the <hi rend="italic">Queen Elizabeth</hi> and the <hi
                        rend="italic">Queen Mary</hi>;<note n="3" xml:id="d710a-40fn3">See <ref
                            target="#d1191">document No. 1191</ref>, <hi rend="italic"
                        >post</hi>.</note> the conversion of 100 vessels by the United Kingdom; the
                    allocation of captured German passenger vessels for United States use in the
                    movement of troops;<note n="4" xml:id="d710a-40fn4">See <ref target="#d1190"
                            >document No. 1190</ref>, <hi rend="italic">post</hi>.</note> the use
                    and possible conversion of the <hi rend="italic">Gripsholm</hi> and the <hi
                        rend="italic">Drottningholm;</hi> American and British trooplift
                        programs;<note n="3" xml:id="d710a-40fn7">See <ref target="#d1191">document
                            No. 1191</ref>, <hi rend="italic">post</hi>.</note> the possible
                    admission of Italy to the United Maritime Authority and the Mediterranean
                    Shipping Board;<note n="5" xml:id="d710a-40fn5">See <ref target="#d1110"
                            >document No. 1110</ref>, <hi rend="italic">post</hi>.</note> possible
                    British payment of charter hire for Italian vessels; the distribution of
                    captured German vessels and their use during the <gloss target="#t_War1"
                        >war</gloss> against Japan;<note n="4" xml:id="d710a-40fn8">See <ref
                            target="#d1190">document No. 1190</ref>, <hi rend="italic"
                        >post</hi>.</note> and problems relating to the striking Polish crews on
                    British-operated Polish vessels.<note n="6" xml:id="d710a-40fn6">See <ref
                            target="#d1124">documents Nos. 1124</ref> and <ref target="#d1125"
                            >1125</ref>, <hi rend="italic">post</hi>.</note>
                </p>
            </div>
